        <updateDate>2019-08-05T17:58:35Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Health Insurance for Former Foster Youth Act <br /></b></p> <p>This bill requires state Medicaid programs to expand coverage&nbsp;for former foster care youth. Specifically,&nbsp;state Medicaid programs must cover individuals who were in foster care at 14 years of age but who subsequently left foster care due to a kinship guardianship. In addition,&nbsp;states must provide such coverage regardless of whether individuals were enrolled in Medicaid while in foster care.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
